<p>According to 
 <xref rid="B6091578" ref-type="bibr">Lin and Zhang (1993)</xref>, 
 <italic>
  <named-content content-type="taxon-name">
   <named-content content-type="genus">Brachymna</named-content>
   <named-content content-type="species">tenuis</named-content>
  </named-content>
 </italic> resembles 
 <italic>
  <named-content content-type="taxon-name">
   <named-content content-type="genus">B.</named-content>
   <named-content content-type="species">castanea</named-content>
  </named-content>
 </italic>. It differs from the latter by the yellowish-brown body colour (Fig. 
 <xref ref-type="fig" rid="F6092365">1</xref>
 <xref ref-type="fig" rid="F6092370">a</xref>, 
 <xref ref-type="fig" rid="F6092371">b</xref>) (ferruginous in 
 <italic>
  <named-content content-type="taxon-name">
   <named-content content-type="genus">B.</named-content>
   <named-content content-type="species">castanea</named-content>
  </named-content>
 </italic>) and the pygophore bearing dentate postero-lateral processes that are obtusely curved from the postero-ventral margin (Fig. 
 <xref ref-type="fig" rid="F6092365">1</xref>
 <xref ref-type="fig" rid="F6092372">c</xref>) (postero-lateral processes make approximately a right angle with the postero-ventral margin in 
 <italic>
  <named-content content-type="taxon-name">
   <named-content content-type="genus">B.</named-content>
   <named-content content-type="species">castanea</named-content>
  </named-content>
 </italic>).
</p>
